# AI Platform Reference Architecture – Production Program

Author: Carlos Alejandro Perez Ceron
Role: AI Platform & FinOps Architect  

---

## Executive Summary

This repository defines a secure, GPU-enabled AI platform architecture deployed on AWS EKS.

The objective is to demonstrate how AI workloads can be deployed with:

- Secure network isolation
- GPU-aware Kubernetes scheduling
- Observability and performance metrics
- Cost-per-inference modeling
- FinOps governance integration

This repository is managed under a structured implementation program visible in the GitHub Projects section.

---

## Architecture Components

- VPC with private subnets
- Private EKS cluster
- CPU node group
- GPU node group (g5.xlarge default)
- Prometheus monitoring
- Grafana dashboards
- Cost modeling scripts
- Threat modeling documentation

---

## Security Principles

- No public EKS endpoint
- IAM least privilege
- IRSA for workloads
- Namespace isolation
- Network policies applied
- Container image scanning documented

---

## FinOps Modeling

Included:

- GPU monthly baseline cost estimator
- Cost per inference calculator
- Reserved vs On-Demand analysis
- GPU underutilization simulation

---

## Observability

Monitored metrics:

- CPU usage
- Memory usage
- GPU utilization
- Request latency
- Error rate
- Cost efficiency ratio

---

## Trade-offs

- GPU nodes increase baseline cost but reduce inference latency.
- Reserved instances improve predictability but reduce flexibility.
- Private clusters increase security posture but add networking complexity.

---

## Future Enhancements

- Spot instance automation
- Multi-cloud deployment model
- AI Survivability scoring
- Cost anomaly detection
